<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,404,429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">Comments</emphasis>
. This species is known from a single male. The chaetotaxy of the abdominal tergites and sternites are unusual within this genus. The pronotal am setae are also minute in 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1042,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="howei">
<emphasis box="[975,1042,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">howei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only in 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1312,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemiflavus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1312,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">hemiflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the ml setae minute. The presence of only two sensoria on antennal segment III is also unusual, but that is shared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Okajima" authorityName="Okajima" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coloratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">H. coloratus</emphasis>
Okajima
</taxonomicName>
from the Ryukyu Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[658,725,512,535]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="486">Japan</collectingCountry>
, a species with a brown pronotum and yellow pterothorax.
</paragraph>
